    public class MORDefinitionIndividual
extends MORIndividualBase
implements MORIndividual.Disjoint<MORDefinitionIndividual>, MORIndividual.Equivalent<MORDefinitionIndividual>
    A basic implementation for an individual with 'same as' and 'different from' individual description.

    This is an example of how use the Semantic.Descriptors for implement am individual that is synchronised w.r.t. to Equivalent and Disjoint instances.
    Its purpose is only to instanciate the MORAxioms.Individuals for the respective descriptions, as well as call both interfaces in the readSemantic() and writeSemantic() methods. All its constructions are based on MORIndividualBase in order to automatically manage a grounding IndividualInstance.
    You may want to use this class (see also MORTypeIndividual and MORLinkIndividual, as well as other classes in the it.emarolab.owloop.aMORDescriptor.utility package) as templates to build a specific MORIndividual descriptor that fits your needs and maximises the OWL synchronisation efficiency for data properties.
